From Aras:

{quote}
On Mac in the diff views you can select whole lines, but clicking again lets select parts of it - that would be useful to have. 

Also, Copy to clipboard working on selected stuff in diff views please!
{/quote}

Copying to clipboard of lines selected in the diff view is done.

From Aras:
{quote}
Dragging repositories into sidebar: would be nice if a shortcut file could also be dragged. I initially dragged a shortcut from desktop to real repo, and wondered why it doesn't work.
{quote}

Just updated to Sourcetree for Mac 4.1.4 (20) and noticed that German Umlauts are not displayed correctly any more in the file contents diff view.

The actual contents of that file are:
{code:java}
special_chars_table = {
  # German
  'Ä','Ae', 'ä','ae',
  'Ö','Oe', 'ö','oe',
  'Ü','ue', 'ü','ue',
  'ß','ss'
}{code}
 It is displayed as (copy-paste):
{code:java}
      special_chars_table = {
        # German
        '˜','Ae', 'î','ae',
        'á','Oe', 'ü','oe',
        'è','ue', 'þ','ue',
        'ë','ss'
      }{code}
